# Portfólio EDU — project conventions

## Stack
- Main site: vanilla HTML/CSS/JS (no bundler). Deploy via GitHub Pages at `cardoso-ix.github.io/Portifolio/`.
- Scripts: Python 3 (`Pillow`, `ReportLab`) in `scripts/`.
- Embedded sub-app: `conversor-unidades/` is a pre-built Vite artifact — do not edit hashed files; rebuild from source repo.

## Content tone
- Portuguese (pt-BR). Lead with Pós Tech Agentes de IA (FIAP + Alura), LLMs, RAG, Make, n8n, CrewAI.
- Public positioning is AI-first; industrial experience may remain in the experience/formation timelines only.

## CSS
- Use existing CSS custom properties in `:root` / `[data-theme="light"]`.
- BEM-like naming: `.section__element`, `.block__element--modifier`.
- Respect `prefers-reduced-motion: reduce` for animations.

## JS
- Keep `main.js` as a single IIFE with `'use strict'`.
- Use passive scroll listeners and `requestAnimationFrame` throttling.
- Bump `?v=` query on `css/style.css`, `js/main.js`, and PDF links when shipping cache-sensitive assets.

## CV generator
- `scripts/generate_cv.py` writes to paths relative to `ROOT` (project folder).
- After editing CV data, run `python scripts/generate_cv.py` and commit `assets/cv_eduardo_cardoso.pdf`.

## Paths
- GitHub Pages base path is `/Portifolio/` — subproject links must account for this.
- Repo remote: `cardoso-ix/Portifolio` (local folder may be `Portifolio-EDU`).
